    rationale: "At rapid heart rates, diastole shortens dramatically. The rapid filling phase (S3) and the atrial kick phase (S4) \u2014 which are normally separated in time \u2014 overlap and merge into a single loud sound called a summation gallop. This is not turbulent flow across the mitral valve (which would produce a murmur, not a gallop), not paradoxical S2 splitting (which involves semilunar valves), and not a pericardial knock (which is a distinct early diastolic sound in constrictive pericarditis, not rate-dependent in this way).",
