    rationale: "An irregularly irregular pulse has no discernible repeating pattern \u2014 the intervals between beats vary chaotically, as in atrial fibrillation. A regularly irregular pulse has a consistent repeating cycle of irregularity, such as bigeminy (normal beat followed by PVC, repeating) or Mobitz I (progressively lengthening PR until a beat is dropped, then repeating). Atrial fibrillation causes only irregularly irregular rhythms. Sinus arrhythmia is a regularly irregular rhythm (varies with respiration), not caused by PVCs.",
