    rationale: "The radial pulse disappearing at 172 mmHg indicates the true systolic pressure is approximately 172 mmHg. The auscultated reading of 138 mmHg likely represents the bottom of an auscultatory gap \u2014 a silent interval where Korotkoff sounds temporarily disappear. The cuff must be re-inflated to at least 20\u201330 mmHg above the palpated systolic pressure (i.e., to ~190\u2013200 mmHg) and slowly deflated to capture the true systolic pressure. Accepting 138 mmHg would represent a 34 mmHg underestimation. Repeating in the opposite arm does not address the auscultatory gap.",
