    rationale: "Mitral regurgitation occurs when the mitral valve fails to close completely during systole, allowing blood to flow backward from the high-pressure left ventricle into the low-pressure left atrium. The left atrium is positioned posterolaterally, so the regurgitant jet \u2014 and therefore the murmur \u2014 radiates to the left axilla. Tricuspid regurgitation radiates to the right sternal border. Aortic regurgitation is diastolic. Pulmonic regurgitation does not radiate to the axilla.",
